-p used here to forward traffic from port 8000 to port 80
-v $(pwd):/var/www/html to mount the current folder where the docker image serves out its web content
php:8.1-apache we use the php docker image version 8.1 apache variant. It means the apache server is built right in enabling us to get up and run and execute PHP code in a single move.


Server Side Security Considerations
Injections, inject malicious content in a server 
-Local File Inlcusion : display a file resident on the server
-Upload file exploits : server-side allows uploading files that can be executed through the web app
-Remote File Inclusion : display files from other servers, injected malicious JavaScript, include fake login pae hosted ny attacker
Cross-site Scripting : lead to execution of malicious JavaScript
-Database injection : server-side allows unsanitized database queries to disclose information
-Server-side request forgery : server-side allows network requests from the application to the internal network
